Review of November 30, 2020 Watchlist (1/2):
$CRM - Sold off on earnings this week due to the announcement of acquiring SLACK for $29.3B in a cash & stock deal. CRM beat on revenue and raises guidance for both 2021 EPS and Revenue. It is likely that this selloff is an overreaction to the news, will continue to monitor CRM for a long term entry opportunity.
$HOLX - Pumped very nicely off our buy zone this week, now testing resistance at 73.70.
$IIPR - Continuing to consolidate but broke below the flag. Pattern is still in tact for the short term. The US passed a bill on Friday that will decriminalize cannabis at the federal level. 
$SNPS - Beat on EPS and Revenue (21% yoyo growth) but is lowering revenue guidance for Q1 2021. SNPS took off nicely on earnings and is now looking to test ATH at 246.
